{"key":"post-8874768","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8874768</id>\n<content>I'd go with the AA 921 to get started.&amp;nbsp; It's plenty large in that it can hold ten 1 quart jars, or around 25 or so half pints.&amp;nbsp; With the money you save over the 941, you can get the rest of the supplies you need.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The sterilizer or canner will work just fine for brf and grain jars. When you move to agar, I'd recommend the canner, since I've had the vacuum a sterilizer develops as it cools, cause my agar to boil over and substrate bags to rupture.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8875584</next>\n<prev>8874583</prev>\n<first>8874405</first>\n<last>8876920</last>\n<when>1220508878</when>\n<utime>09/04/08 09:14 AM</utime>\n</post>"}